The '''Abridon Nationalists''' were a resistance group fighting to liberate their homeworld of [[Abridon/Legends|Abridon]] from the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]]. In [[3 ABY/Legends|3 ABY]], they were able to [[Uprising on Abridon|seize]] the planet in cooperation with [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] forces. The [[Abridon Government Council]] opened negotiations to join the Rebel Alliance, which was represented by five dignitaries, including [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] hero [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]].

[[File:Flatt.jpg|thumb|left|[[Hamman Flatt]], leader of the Abridon Nationalists]]
However, their control was short-lived. Within three days [[Grand General/Legends|Grand General]] [[Malcor Brashin]] and [[General/Legends|General]] [[Brenn Tantor]] arrived on the Imperial [[Star Destroyer/Legends|Star Destroyer]] [[Inquisitor (Star Destroyer)|''Inquisitor'']]. Tantor landed on the outskirts of Abridon's [[Abridon capital city|capital]] and swiftly [[Massacre on Abridon|evicted]] the Nationalists and their Rebel allies, recapturing the [[Abridon Government Center|Government Center]] and the capital's Imperial base. In the attack, he captured a Nationalist leader, [[Hamman Flatt]]. Flatt, the planet's [[Lieutenant governor/Legends|lieutenant governor]], offered information to Tantor in hope of mercy, giving up the dignitaries. Flatt was put in a [[Abridon holding camp|prison camp]] and Tantor was able to capture the dignitaries, including Skywalker, and completely wipe out the Rebel presence.

Even with the Alliance gone, the Nationalists remained. The industrial city of [[Sayan]] became their stronghold. Nationalists engaged in months of battles with Imperial forces until the Empire had had enough. The Empire placed artillery platforms next to the [[Abridon Shipyard|shipyards]] and began systematically leveling the city.

Into this situation stepped Brenn Tantor yet again. Now having defected to the Alliance, he [[Liberation of Abridon|captured]] the Government Center yet again, freed Flatt, captured the Sayan shipyards, and completely exterminated the Empire's presence in Sayan. The Abridon Nationalists gladly joined the Alliance, just in time to provide [[RZ-1 A-wing interceptor/Legends|A-wing]] fighters for the imminent [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]].

